// #2394: a user-written block wrapped AROUND an array literal source
// (`for x in { [<array literal>] } { ... }`) must exit clean, matching the
// bare literal source's #2356 fix.
//
// The array literal desugars to a synthetic `Block` whose tail is a
// `BindingRef` to a named temp (`__hew_array_N`) that keeps its own
// scope-exit drop. Wrapping the literal in one more user block nests a
// SECOND `Block` layer around that shape: the outer block's own tail is the
// inner array-literal desugar block, not yet a bare `BindingRef`. Peeling
// only one `Block` layer left the inner block intact as the `VecIter`
// source, so MIR's CowShare place-source match still failed to recognise
// it, the cursor was wrongly treated as the sole owner, and its scope-exit
// release double-freed the temp's buffer alongside the temp's own drop —
// an invalid free the compiled native binary aborts on (SIGABRT via glibc
// `free(): invalid pointer`). Asserted against the BUILT NATIVE binary so
// the double free cannot hide behind `hew run`'s masking.
fn main() {
    for x in { [99, 6, 100] } {
        println(x);
    }
}
